cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on video recognition and reinforcement learning, which are both subfields of computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel event-driven representation that can be used for fast real-time inference and learning, which suggests that it may also be relevant to subfields such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions applications such as game-playing and virtual robotics, which suggests that it may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
